SIMPLE: sprinkle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sprinkle
<hw>Sprin"kle</hw> <pr>(spr⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧"k'l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Sprinkled</conjf>
<pr>(-k'ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Sprinkling</conjf>
<pr>(-kl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>sprenkelen</ets>, freq.
of <ets>sprengen</ets> to sprinkle, to scatter, AS. <ets>sprengan</ets>,
properly, to make to spring, causative of <ets>springan</ets> to spring;
akin to D. <ets>sprenkelen</ets> to sprinkle, G. <ets>sprengen</ets>.
See <er>Spring</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>, and cf. <er>Sprent</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To scatter in small drops or particles, as water, seed,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To scatter on; to disperse something over in small
drops or particles; to besprinkle; <as>as, to <ex>sprinkle</ex> the
earth with water; to <ex>sprinkle</ex> a floor with sand</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To baptize by the application of a few drops, or a
small quantity, of water; hence, to cleanse; to purify.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Having our hearts <qex>sprinkled</qex> from an evil
conscience.</q> <rj><qau>Heb. x. 22.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprinkle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sprinkle
<hw>Sprin"kle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To scatter a
liquid, or any fine substance, so that it may fall in
particles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And the priest shall . . . <qex>sprinkle</qex> of the oil with his
finger seven times before the Lord.</q> <rj><qau>Lev. xiv.
16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To rain moderately, or with scattered drops falling
now and then; <as>as, it <ex>sprinkles</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To fly or be scattered in small drops or
particles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprinkle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sprinkle
<hw>Sprin"kle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small quantity
scattered, or sparsely distributed; a sprinkling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A utensil for sprinkling; a sprinkler.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprinkler</ent>⟦br⟧
